One of the first steps in your house hunt is getting pre-approved!

And to debunk another myth, pre-approvals do not tank your credit! The impact is VERY small and the dip in your credit score will be temporary. And the advantages of getting preapproved far outweigh the small hit to your score.

If you’re looking to buy or if you’re just curious on what you can get approved for, let me know and I can get you connected to an amazing mortgage lender!

Higher interest rates aren’t always a bad thing! Lower rates means higher demand and higher homes prices. When the rates are low, the demand goes down giving buyers more purchasing power and more room to negotiate. Also it’s a no brainer that all buyers want to avoid multiple offer situations! Check out this real life example for a home in Frisco ISD:

2022 -
List price: $900,000
Sold for: $950,000
Down payment: 95,000
Interest Rate: 4%
Monthly Payment: $4082

July 2023 - 
List Price: $950,000
Sold for: $900,000 
Down payment: 90,000
Sellers concessions: $40,000 (for 3-2-1 buy down)
Monthly payment with 7.25% interest: $5,583
Monthly payment with 4.25% interest: $4,024

Yall that’s $1000 in savings a month! Buyers - this is your market and I’m here to help you win. Shoot me a DM to get started or if you have any questions 🤍
